<article id="post-12684" class="post-12684 page type-page status-publish hentry">



	<div class="entry-content2">
		<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid vc_row_visible"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-8 text-left"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element " >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-50e098e6 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="50e098e6" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-50e098e6 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="50e098e6" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
<h3>Course Objectives</h3>
<p>Aligning your business with suppliers that operate at consistently high levels of quality is necessary to keeping your own organization performing at a high level. This supplier quality training can help you understand how to choose suppliers, how to maintain fewer, higher-quality partnerships, and how to manage the relationships you have with your suppliers.</p>
<p><strong>Participants will learn to:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Provide an overview of how supplier quality can be managed.</li>
<li>Provide an overview of how supplier evaluation is carried out.</li>
<li>Explain supplier relations management</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-5bf508d8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="5bf508d8" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
<h3>Target Audience</h3>
<p>This programme involves a wide range of learning approaches, including self – assessment, case studies, small group activities and discussions, interactive lectures, experimental learning group assignments and exercises and presentation and critique.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-70129582 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="70129582" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
<h3>Methodology</h3>
<p>This Live Online / Virtual Training session will be conducted via a Live Streaming Platform in which the trainer will use interactive lecture and slide presentation to cover the modules stated below.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="elementor-element elementor-element-7d521bfc elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor" data-id="7d521bfc" data-element_type="widget" data-widget_type="text-editor.default">
<div class="elementor-widget-container">
<div class="elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix">
<h3>Course Modules</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Module 1 – Importance Of Supplier Quality</strong><br />
– Purchasing costs as a percent of Sales<br />
– Motivating forces – Supply savings example<br />
– Inventory hides problems<br />
– Traditional purchasing process</li>
<li><strong>Module 2 – Supply Chain Management</strong><br />
– The supply chain<br />
– Basic relationship between buyer and supplier<br />
– Relative emphasis of quality in purchasing decisions</li>
<li><strong>Module 3 – Supplier Strategy</strong><br />
– Many supplier strategy<br />
– Multiple suppliers vs single source<br />
– Few suppliers strategy<br />
– Internal vs external suppliers<br />
– Developing partnership with suppliers – policies<br />
